Below is the **complete system-level definition and flow design** for:

# üî∑ LOGIC 4 ‚Äì Tender Publication & Market Visibility Logic

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ PURPOSE OF THIS LOGIC

This logic governs:

* How tenders are published
* Who can see them
* When they become visible
* How they are distributed across the marketplace
* How fairness and equal access are ensured

It directly impacts:

* Competition levels
* Supplier participation
* Market transparency
* Anti-corruption safeguards
* Reduction of market fragmentation

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ HIGH-LEVEL FLOW OVERVIEW

```
Tender Draft Approved (from Logic 3)
        ‚Üì
Pre-Publication Validation
        ‚Üì
Visibility Rule Configuration
        ‚Üì
Supplier Eligibility Matching
        ‚Üì
Publication Execution
        ‚Üì
Notification & Distribution
        ‚Üì
Clarification Window Activation
        ‚Üì
Ongoing Monitoring & Fairness Enforcement
        ‚Üì
Submission Deadline Lock
```

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ PRE-PUBLICATION VALIDATION

Before a tender can go live, the system checks:

### A. Structural Completeness

* Evaluation criteria locked
* Budget defined
* Timeline valid
* Scope complete

### B. Governance Checks

* All approvals completed (Logic 2 RBAC enforced)
* No pending compliance flags
* No conflict-of-interest flags

### C. Fairness Validation

* Minimum response time met
* No discriminatory eligibility criteria
* Amendment rules configured

If any validation fails ‚Üí publication blocked.

---

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ VISIBILITY MODELS

The system must support multiple visibility types:

---

## üîπ 1. Open Public Tender

* Visible to all verified suppliers
* Searchable marketplace listing
* Appears in public feed

Use case:

* High transparency procurements
* Government tenders

---

## üîπ 2. Category-Restricted Tender

Visible only to suppliers:

* Registered under specific category codes
* With matching certifications
* Meeting minimum trust level

Matching logic:

```
IF Supplier.Category = Tender.Category
AND Supplier.TrustLevel ‚â• RequiredLevel
THEN Show Tender
```

---

## üîπ 3. Geographic-Restricted Tender

Visible only to suppliers:

* Operating in selected regions
* Licensed in required jurisdiction

Used for:

* Local compliance
* Regional supply requirements

---

## üîπ 4. Prequalified / Closed Tender

Visible only to:

* Pre-approved supplier list
* Framework agreement participants
* Invitation-only vendors

System ensures:

* Invitation list locked
* All invited suppliers notified simultaneously
* No late additions without audit trail

---

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ SUPPLIER MATCHING ENGINE

When tender is published, the system runs:

### Matching Criteria:

* Category codes
* Industry classification
* Geographic presence
* Certifications
* Financial capacity
* Trust level
* Risk score threshold

Matching produces:

* Eligible Supplier Pool
* Suggested Supplier List
* Automatic notification group

---

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ MARKET DISTRIBUTION MECHANISMS

Upon publication:

### A. Internal Marketplace Feed

* Appears in supplier dashboard
* Sorted by relevance

### B. Notification Engine

* Email alerts
* In-app alerts
* SMS (optional)
* API distribution (if integrated partners)

### C. Public Portal Listing (if open)

* Public search index
* SEO indexing
* RSS feed export

---

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ FAIRNESS & ANTI-ADVANTAGE CONTROLS

The system enforces:

### Simultaneous Visibility

* All eligible suppliers see tender at same timestamp.

### No Early Access

* Drafts cannot be previewed externally.
* Internal users cannot share secure preview links.

### Amendment Rules

If tender amended:

```
Amendment Published
        ‚Üì
All Suppliers Notified
        ‚Üì
Deadline Auto-Extended (if material change)
```

---

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ TIMING WINDOW LOGIC

Mandatory timeline enforcement:

### Minimum Bid Period Rules

Example:

| Tender Value | Minimum Response Time |
| ------------ | --------------------- |
| Low          | 7 days                |
| Medium       | 14 days               |
| High         | 30 days               |

System prevents:

* Artificially short deadlines
* Retroactive deadline changes
* Deadline shortening after publish

---

# 9Ô∏è‚É£ CLARIFICATION WINDOW MANAGEMENT

After publication:

```
Clarification Period Opens
        ‚Üì
Suppliers Submit Questions
        ‚Üì
Questions Logged (Anonymous View)
        ‚Üì
Buyer Responds
        ‚Üì
Response Visible to All Suppliers
```

Controls:

* No private answers allowed
* All Q&A logged
* Time-stamped
* Immutable

Ensures:

* No supplier receives privileged information

---

# üîü MARKET FRAGMENTATION REDUCTION LOGIC

To reduce fragmentation:

### Unified Categorization System

* Standard taxonomy across marketplace
* Prevents duplicate classifications

### Intelligent Recommendation Engine

* Suggests tenders to SMEs
* Suggests smaller lots for small suppliers

### Lot Structuring Option

Tender can be split into lots:

* Lot 1: Hardware
* Lot 2: Installation
* Lot 3: Maintenance

Enables:

* SME participation
* Increased competition

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ ELIGIBILITY FILTERING DURING VISIBILITY

System hides tenders from suppliers if:

* Trust level below threshold
* Sanctioned entity
* Suspended account
* Conflict-of-interest flag
* Category mismatch

But system logs:

* Why tender was not shown
* For audit purposes

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ SEARCH & DISCOVERY LOGIC

Suppliers can:

* Filter by category
* Filter by value range
* Filter by region
* Filter by deadline
* Filter by buyer organization

Search ranking factors:

* Category relevance
* Supplier past performance match
* Location proximity
* Capacity match

No ranking bias toward specific suppliers.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ AUDIT & TRANSPARENCY REQUIREMENTS

For every publication:

Log:

* Publish timestamp
* Visibility type
* Eligible supplier count
* Notification batch ID
* Amendment history
* Deadline history

All stored in immutable audit log.

---

